Here.

254
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:28,570
There are no seats after coming back
from playing basketball.

255
00:18:28,570 --> 00:18:31,330
That punk.
When we saved him a seat...

256
00:18:34,820 --> 00:18:36,490
Why is he sitting there?

257
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:38,800
- So what?
- What do you mean by 'so what'?

258
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:40,330
True.

259
00:18:41,090 --> 00:18:42,850
You like basketball?

260
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:46,930
Yeah, I do.
On top of that, I'm good at it.

261
00:18:55,860 --> 00:19:00,300
If you look carefully, our class is a corporation.

262
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:03,610
Hui Yeong is the president.
The people next to him are his followers.

263
00:19:03,610 --> 00:19:07,690
If he finishes eating and leaves,
they'll probably all get up to follow him.

264
00:19:07,690 --> 00:19:09,720
It's funny, right?

265
00:19:10,510 --> 00:19:13,410
Boys are... Seriously...

266
00:19:13,410 --> 00:19:17,130
Even if you get just two together,
they're busy figuring out their ranks.

267
00:19:20,730 --> 00:19:23,130
- What about you?
- Huh?

268
00:19:23,130 --> 00:19:24,900
What are you like?

269
00:19:28,570 --> 00:19:30,390
What do you think I'm like?

270
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:35,190
What are they doing?
Sizing each other up?

271
00:19:35,190 --> 00:19:37,270
Well, just...

272
00:19:37,270 --> 00:19:38,860
Just?

273
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:45,760
Just... a nice basketball player?

274
00:19:50,590 --> 00:19:52,100
Correct.

275
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:56,140
What's a nice basketball player?
I've never heard that before.

276
00:19:56,140 --> 00:19:58,120
Joon Woo!

277
00:19:58,120 --> 00:20:02,990
You were no joke at your last school.
Not just this, but you must have been good at a lot of things.

278
00:20:02,990 --> 00:20:06,390
What are you saying, Jo Sang Hoon, while we're eating? Go.

279
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:10,150
Sorry, bro.

280
00:20:10,150 --> 00:20:12,030
Eat a lot.

281
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:34,440
What did Jo Sang Hoon say?

282
00:20:36,230 --> 00:20:38,170
He said to eat the peas, too.

283
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:43,540
Well, that's a nice thing to say.

284
00:20:45,890 --> 00:20:47,690
You're done eating?

285
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,930
Take your time eating.
Slowly.

286
00:21:09,820 --> 00:21:11,670
Go ahead first.

287
00:21:18,130 --> 00:21:20,010
You're scared, right?

288
00:21:21,470 --> 00:21:25,530
That incident, that I will tell on you to the transfer student.

289
00:21:25,530 --> 00:21:27,320
What incident?

290
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,620
Look at you pretending not to know.

291
00:21:30,620 --> 00:21:34,730
Right.
You have to. It's more fun that way.

292
00:21:34,730 --> 00:21:37,120
Jo Sang Hoon.

293
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:38,590
- Do you know something?
- What?

294
00:21:38,590 --> 00:21:39,470
What?

295
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:42,510
You laughing like this,...

296
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:44,790
is really irritating.

297
00:21:44,790 --> 00:21:47,640
I don't know what you're trying to say,

298
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,840
but do whatever you want.

299
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:53,230
Whether it's telling on me or whatever.

300
00:21:59,430 --> 00:22:02,880
Okay, to be fair, let's do rock paper scissors
between the female and male representatives.

301
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:07,320
Losing team writes down the names
and the winning team picks, okay?

302
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:10,330
There are more guys.

303
00:22:10,330 --> 00:22:12,750
It can't be helped.
The rest can pair up with themselves.

304
00:22:12,750 --> 00:22:15,350
It's nerve-wracking.

305
00:22:15,350 --> 00:22:16,960
Okay, start.

306
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:23,640
♬ Anything I don't want to hear,
everything you have to say ♬

307
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:28,110
♬ But when you start giving instructions,
I just gotta walk away ♬

308
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:33,890
♬ It just goes in one ear and out the other ♬

309
00:22:34,580 --> 00:22:40,160
♬ It reminds me just a little too much
of my sweet mother. ♬

310
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:43,490
♬ I never could listen to what she had to say ♬

311
00:22:43,490 --> 00:22:45,270
I had to run for cover.

312
00:22:45,270 --> 00:22:50,910
♬ It just goes in one ear and out the other ♬

313
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:57,560
♬ You like talking about your feelings ♬

314
00:22:57,560 --> 00:23:00,360
♬ I guess you always will ♬

315
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:05,800
♬ But I don't really wanna feel like I'm on Dr. Phil ♬

316
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:11,560
♬ You say it'll make us closer; it's driving us apart ♬

317
00:23:18,010 --> 00:23:22,410
Lee Gi Tae?
You're so lucky, he's really good at English.

318
00:23:22,410 --> 00:23:24,610
Next, Da Huin.

319
00:23:24,610 --> 00:23:25,810
You're not going to pray?

320
00:23:25,810 --> 00:23:30,060
I prayed before the PE exam and I got paired up with Pil Sang.

321
00:23:30,060 --> 00:23:32,010
Please, as long as it's not Yoon Pil Sang.

322
00:23:32,010 --> 00:23:34,810
Hey, hey, hey, I don't want you either.

323
00:23:34,810 --> 00:23:37,920
- So, what?
- Same to you.

324
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:43,100
Is it Yoon Pil Sang again?

325
00:23:44,860 --> 00:23:47,670
Oh, Jeong Oh Jae?

326
00:23:47,670 --> 00:23:50,460
It's me?
Let's do well, Da Huin.

327
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:52,020
Okay.

328
00:23:53,050 --> 00:23:55,440
Next, Ro Mi.

329
00:24:01,530 --> 00:24:04,540
Why? Who is it?

330
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:08,420
- Who is it?
- Yoon Pil Sang!

331
00:24:10,020 --> 00:24:12,830
Yes!

332
00:24:12,830 --> 00:24:15,420
Ro Mi! Ro Mi!

333
00:24:15,420 --> 00:24:17,730
She must hate it!

334
00:24:18,880 --> 00:24:19,880
Oh, Chan Yeol.

335
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:22,040
It's Chan Yeol.

336
00:24:25,430 --> 00:24:27,320
Sit, sit.
You do it first.

337
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:30,940
Okay, then I'll go first.

338
00:24:33,820 --> 00:24:37,060
This has a unique shape.

339
00:24:37,060 --> 00:24:38,650
It's a present.

340
00:24:38,650 --> 00:24:40,800
Forget it.

341
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:43,550
Take it. I have a lot.

342
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:57,330
Who is in charge of recyling in your class?

343
00:25:07,130 --> 00:25:09,090
What are you doing here?

344
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:12,480
I'm on duty here.

345
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:15,250
You're not preparing for English?
Free talking?

346
00:25:15,250 --> 00:25:17,150
I should.

347
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:19,180
Who picked me?

348
00:25:23,730 --> 00:25:25,950
Nobody picked me?

349
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:32,130
Choi Joon Woo.

350
00:25:44,860 --> 00:25:47,170
When are you free?

351
00:25:48,730 --> 00:25:49,830
Now is a little...

352
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:52,720
Wow, I picked you, and you're playing hard to get?

353
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:55,610
I'm not playing hard to get after you picked me.

354
00:25:56,770 --> 00:26:00,030
I have to go to my part-time job now.

355
00:26:00,770 --> 00:26:02,410
That...

356
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:07,530
I'm still too new to tell you about my personal situation.

357
00:26:09,830 --> 00:26:12,940
I'm not free right now either.

358
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:14,670
I have to go somewhere.

359
00:26:16,430 --> 00:26:18,920
Oh.

360
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:20,770
Okay then.

361
00:26:20,770 --> 00:26:22,710
I'll text you later.

362
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:28,570
Choi Joon Woo.
What's your dream?

363
00:26:31,450 --> 00:26:33,060
Dream?

364
00:26:35,420 --> 00:26:36,520
I don't know.

365
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:40,650
Huh? What?
How are—

366
00:26:41,910 --> 00:26:43,440
Okay.

367
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:48,970
Then for now, just think of anything
because we have to take the test. Okay?

368
00:26:59,970 --> 00:27:01,680
Bye.

369
00:27:04,970 --> 00:27:06,410
There are a few missing.

370
00:27:06,410 --> 00:27:08,030
Are you done?
I'll hand it in.

371
00:27:08,030 --> 00:27:10,260
Please hand it in if you're done writing.

372
00:27:12,130 --> 00:27:13,780
Wait.

373
00:27:13,780 --> 00:27:17,960
Why is it taking so long to write down names?

374
00:27:41,790 --> 00:27:44,130
Choi Joon Woo's kind of cute.

375
00:27:44,130 --> 00:27:45,830
He even knows to put a code on it.

376
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:49,800
For references, I checked all the quotes.

377
00:27:52,530 --> 00:27:55,050
Hey, Ma Hui Yeong!

378
00:27:55,050 --> 00:27:59,020
How can you just leave like that?
We're partners.

379
00:27:59,020 --> 00:28:01,680
Yeah, let's do well.

380
00:28:03,560 --> 00:28:07,740
What should we do?
Let's go to the cafeteria and talk about it over a latte.

381
00:28:07,740 --> 00:28:09,940
What should I do?
I have to go right now.

382
00:28:09,940 --> 00:28:12,860
I'll make the script by tomorrow.
Your part too.

383
00:28:12,860 --> 00:28:17,260
You'll just have to memorize it.
Let's match everything up on test day. Bye.

384
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:20,660
How can you just leave like that?

385
00:28:20,660 --> 00:28:24,540
Do you know my dream?
You don't know anything about me.

386
00:28:24,540 --> 00:28:27,810
Don't worry.
I'll make sure we get a 100.

387
00:28:27,810 --> 00:28:30,110
Just prepare for the midterms well.

388
00:28:31,450 --> 00:28:35,330
Hey, Ma Hui Yeong! Hey!

389
00:28:35,330 --> 00:28:37,430
Thank you!

390
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:42,670
Hello.

391
00:28:42,670 --> 00:28:44,820
Park Yeong Bae, why are you coming now?

392
00:28:44,820 --> 00:28:47,790
She's been waiting for you since earlier.

393
00:28:47,790 --> 00:28:50,000
- Mom.
- You're arriving late.

394
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:53,690
That's what I'm saying.
He's always five minutes late.

395
00:28:56,660 --> 00:29:00,430
Choi Joon Woo, you can't be like that
when you're working for someone.

396
00:29:00,430 --> 00:29:04,000
You should come 15 minutes early,
and get in the right mindset,

397
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:06,790
and prepare yourself for work.

398
00:29:06,790 --> 00:29:11,550
Mom. Did something happen?
Why all of a sudden?

399
00:29:11,550 --> 00:29:14,570
I had something to do, and I had time left.

400
00:29:14,570 --> 00:29:16,250
Then why didn't you go home instead?

401
00:29:16,250 --> 00:29:21,380
You're working here, so why would I?
I have to go back soon.

402
00:29:21,380 --> 00:29:23,310
Let's go eat.

403
00:29:24,260 --> 00:29:25,350
I have to work.

404
00:29:25,350 --> 00:29:27,570
She already got permission from the boss.

405
00:29:27,570 --> 00:29:30,910
Of course, it needed some of my input as well.

406
00:29:30,910 --> 00:29:32,620
It's good.

407
00:29:32,620 --> 00:29:34,130
It's good?

408
00:29:34,620 --> 00:29:37,170
Eat some.

409
00:29:40,550 --> 00:29:45,730
You're not...
Because of the watch incident,

410
00:29:45,730 --> 00:29:48,590
you're not losing self-confidence at school, are you?

411
00:29:48,590 --> 00:29:50,150
Don't worry, I'm not.

412
00:29:50,150 --> 00:29:55,040
Right, since the truth will come out someday.

413
00:29:55,830 --> 00:29:59,870
Right. You're not keeping in touch
with the kids from the last school, are you?

414
00:29:59,870 --> 00:30:02,510
Jeong Woo. Sin Jeong Woo.

415
00:30:02,510 --> 00:30:04,880
- Jeong Woo hasn't called?
- No.

416
00:30:06,860 --> 00:30:12,170
But then again, he has to have
a conscience after making you transfer.

417
00:30:12,170 --> 00:30:14,770
He's not a bad kid.
You know that.

418
00:30:14,770 --> 00:30:19,540
I know.
I liked him a lot, too.

419
00:30:24,350 --> 00:30:29,400
When I think about that day,

420
00:30:30,420 --> 00:30:36,150
it's so unfair and upsetting.

421
00:30:36,150 --> 00:30:39,900
Mom.

422
00:30:39,900 --> 00:30:42,970
Okay, I'm not crying.

423
00:30:42,970 --> 00:30:46,780
Anyway, you really...

424
00:30:46,780 --> 00:30:49,400
Just study hard from now on, too.

425
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:52,040
Don't get involved in things. Got it?

426
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:54,090
Okay.

427
00:30:54,100 --> 00:30:57,800
- Promise.
- Promise.

428
00:30:57,800 --> 00:30:59,860
Don't cry.

429
00:31:04,490 --> 00:31:09,430
Mom. You came because you were worried about me, right?
Not because you had something to do?

430
00:31:10,810 --> 00:31:11,930
No.

431
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:15,500
- You're lying.
- I am not.

432
00:31:20,190 --> 00:31:21,950
Let's eat.

433
00:31:39,130 --> 00:31:41,970
Why is this so hard?

434
00:31:51,530 --> 00:31:54,530
Let's do your best, Soo Bin.

435
00:31:56,610 --> 00:31:58,470
Go, Mom.
You'll be late for the bus.

436
00:31:58,470 --> 00:32:00,820
Let's walk a little more first.

437
00:32:01,950 --> 00:32:05,130
I told you to move your hair off your forehead.

438
00:32:05,130 --> 00:32:06,380
- Just a little bit.
- I'll do it.

439
00:32:06,380 --> 00:32:08,380
No, it's better if you can see it.

440
00:32:08,380 --> 00:32:10,340
I'll do it.

441
00:32:16,730 --> 00:32:19,560
Hello.

442
00:32:19,560 --> 00:32:22,960
Is she in your class?
Hi, I'm Joon Woo's mom.

443
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:25,010
Oh. Hello.

444
00:32:25,010 --> 00:32:26,390
Hell...o.

445
00:32:26,390 --> 00:32:28,090
Hello.

446
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:36,450
Then we're busy, so...
See you again.

447
00:32:36,450 --> 00:32:38,370
Bye.

448
00:32:42,170 --> 00:32:45,240
Who is that?
He's cute.

449
00:32:45,240 --> 00:32:48,120
He's a new transfer student in our class.

450
00:32:48,120 --> 00:32:50,360
Mom.

451
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:52,050
So embarrassing.

452
00:32:52,050 --> 00:32:54,310
I think that was a real bag.

453
00:32:54,310 --> 00:32:57,100
That's a fake.

454
00:32:57,100 --> 00:32:59,200
She must be embarrassed, right?

455
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:01,070
But still, people carry them around.

456
00:33:01,070 --> 00:33:06,230
They said the real one costs over 10 million won.
Are they rich?

457
00:33:06,230 --> 00:33:07,180
I don't know.

458
00:33:07,180 --> 00:33:09,470
But is that really his mom?
She's so young.

459
00:33:09,470 --> 00:33:10,970
I don't know.
Let's go.

460
00:33:10,970 --> 00:33:12,820
Isn't he too handsome?

461
00:33:12,820 --> 00:33:13,860
I-I don't know.

462
00:33:13,860 --> 00:33:17,010
Class is on a whole another level.

463
00:33:17,010 --> 00:33:19,040
I should be careful.

464
00:33:26,810 --> 00:33:30,400
No, I really can't speak English.

465
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:33,780
You're basically a pro at this level.

466
00:33:33,780 --> 00:33:36,820
I think I met a good partner.

467
00:33:39,490 --> 00:33:41,290
Where are you?

468
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:47,050
I'm waiting for Hui Yeong.

469
00:33:51,590 --> 00:33:53,690
What do I do?

470
00:33:53,690 --> 00:33:58,580
Oh Jae thinks he met a good partner.

471
00:33:58,630 --> 00:34:00,110
Be quiet.

472
00:34:00,110 --> 00:34:01,860
She's acting like she's going to marry him.

473
00:34:01,860 --> 00:34:03,380
I'm here.

474
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:07,100
Soo Bin, where were you?

475
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:13,210
Your mom came by the school, right?

476
00:34:13,210 --> 00:34:15,860
She wanted to look for an academy.

477
00:34:15,860 --> 00:34:18,460
Your mom is...

478
00:34:19,300 --> 00:34:23,060
Your free talking for English,
what are you going to do? Choi Joon Woo?

479
00:34:24,140 --> 00:34:25,730
That's right.

480
00:34:25,730 --> 00:34:26,910
So annoying.

481
00:34:26,910 --> 00:34:29,630
How am I supposed to do it with Pil Sang?

482
00:34:29,630 --> 00:34:32,710
Choi Joon Woo won't be easy either.

483
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:37,070
- Work hard.
- Bye.

484
00:34:47,190 --> 00:34:48,350
Choi Joon Woo,

485
00:34:48,350 --> 00:34:52,490
